docs.lead_paragraph: The Salt Lake mail arrived last night under charge of Mr. CAARLES GILKRY, making the trip in thirty days. He reports that provisions are very scarce in Salt Lake City. The trains of Mormon emigrants were arriving daily, when he left, in pretty good condition.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; THE DUTCH REFORMED CHURCH. Laying of the Corner-Stone of Hertzog Theological Hall, New-Brunswick. MUNICIPAL. LAW INTELLIGENCE.

docs.lead_paragraph: The ceremony of laying the cornor-stone of a new Theological Seminary for the education of young men designed for the ministry of the Dutch Reformed Church, took place yesterday (Thursday) at New-Brunswick.

docs.lead_paragraph: Condition of the Medical Profession among the Ancients. At the Anniversary Meeting of the Academy of Medicine held last evening in the large chapel of the University, a lecture on the "Condition of the Medical Profession among the Ancients," was delivered by Dr. JOHN WATSON. The attendance was large and comprised a few ladies.
